The Roewe W5 is a mid-size luxury SUV manufactured by Roewe in China, first unveiled at the Auto Shanghai exhibition in 2011. It is based on the SsangYong Kyron and is sold only in China.
The W5 features a 1.8-liter four-cylinder turbo engine with 119 kW (162 PS; 160 bhp) that is also used in the Roewe 350 and 550 and is also available in a four-wheel drive only 3.2-liter six-cylinder engine producing 215 kW (292 PS; 288 bhp).
